public class DLGraph extends Object
This class represents a mutable directed labelled graph. A graph is a collection of nodes connected by edges. A node has data, that will be used as its identifier. No two nodes can have the same data. An edge connects two nodes, and flows in one direction - from a 'parent' node, to a 'child' node. Multiple edges can flow between a parent and a child. However, no two edges from the same parent to child nodes can have the same edge label. Abstract Invariant: Only graphs with two or more nodes can have edges No two nodes can have the same data No two edges between the same parent and child nodes can have the same label.
